Rous County was named in honour of Admiral Henry John Rous (1795-1877).

Rous County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located at the north-east tip of the state. It is bordered on the north by the border with Queensland and on the south by the Richmond River . It contains Lismore , Byron Bay and Murwillumbah .
